<h2>Conclusions</h2>
	<p>
		Most participants found some use in this system and all were able to complete all of their tasks, even if they made mistakes in the process. Ease of use and general usefulness is very important for the system. If it’s too difficult it will pull people out of the game and be more work than it’s worth which is something the project has emphasized from the beginning. The study identified several recommendations that will help eliminate the problems that remain but further testing would be needed to ensure that they are successful. 
	</p>

